  "notes": [
    {
      "id": "note_36",
      "text": "Models a binary outcome (yIN) from one or more predictors (xIN) by iteratively-reweighted least squares. The outcome may be numeric 0/1 or a two-level category (the second level, alphabetically, is taken as the positive class = 1). Reports one row per term: the coefficient (log-odds), standard error, Wald z and p-value, odds ratio and its 95% confidence interval, plus the model log-likelihood, likelihood-ratio test against the null and McFadden pseudo-R². It warns on non-convergence, which usually signals separation (a predictor splits the outcome cleanly). Estimates match statsmodels. Cox 1958.",
